description:
&lt;p&gt;Applicants are invited to join a team undertaking a range of tasks ensuring the accurate coding of patient pathways including appointments, diagnoses, treatments and operative procedures.&lt;br /&gt;The post holder will be required to work strictly within the Government’s Access targets ensuring the accurate administration of patients pathway. Knowledge of patient record systems/data bases with proven experience over 2 years plus previous admin/clerical experience – 2 years or more&lt;br /&gt;Ideally you will have a knowledge of the 18 week Referral to Treatment pathway&lt;br /&gt;Well-developed Interpersonal skills – able to converse in a positive manner at all levels. Be dependable with a flexible attitude to work and able to work on your own initiative.&lt;br /&gt;Duties will include, managing the collection and input of vital data onto a computerised system and keeping all patient information accurate and up-to-date.&lt;br /&gt;You must possess strong organisational skills, be able to deliver objectives within an agreed timeframe, excellent people and communication skills to maintain effective communication links, and have a flexible approach to the evolving needs of the service. Applicants should ideally have experience of healthcare services.&lt;br /&gt;It is essential that you possess excellent keyboard skills and expereince of administering data bases.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lynda Webb&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Outpatient Manager&lt;/p&gt;
